name: Ben and Sand

reviews.review_text:
I had a wonderful dining experience at Ben and Sand. The food was delicious, and the highlight for me was their tandoori dishes—perfectly cooked, flavorful, and with just the right amount of spice. It’s clear they’ve mastered the art of tandoori cooking.

Another standout was the fish fry—crispy on the outside, tender on the inside, and incredibly fresh. The quality of the fish and the variety of choices available were impressive. You can tell they prioritize using fresh ingredients, which really makes a difference.

The overall ambiance was warm and inviting, and the service was friendly and attentive. Whether you’re craving tandoori specialties or fresh seafood, Ben and Sand is definitely worth a visit!

Had visited this place for dinner .Had seafood fried rice, chicken Manchuria gravy, and Mussel fry.Food is okay
Car parking should not be an issue. Around 4 min from inox margao.
They charge 2% on credit card payment ,which is illegal as far as I know.
Service was fast. Ambiance is okay

Ben and Sands is a must visit place for us every time we are in Goa that is an average of 1 trip a year

The food is good.  Prices very affordable- not the tourist hiked up rates.  This place is also frequented by the locals

Service is good but it takes about 10 to 15 minutes for your off beat dishes to be served .

Ambience is good
Parking plenty on the road

description:
**Restaurant Review: Ben and Sand, Colva, Goa**

Nestled in the charming coastal village of Colva, Goa, Ben and Sand has garnered a solid reputation with an overall rating of 4.0 from an impressive total of 2,889 reviews. Renowned for their delectable seafood offerings, as well as popular tandoori dishes and crispy chicken, this restaurant has become a favorite among both locals and tourists, drawing attention with tags like *seafood* (67 mentions), *tandoori* (58), *crispy chicken* (26), and *prawns* (25) dominating customer feedback.

### Ambiance & Design
As you step into Ben and Sand, you are greeted by a warm and inviting ambiance that perfectly complements its coastal location. Reviewers appreciate the casual yet cozy design, which features soft lighting and rustic decor—a visual treat evident in the accompanying images showcasing well-spaced tables adorned with colorful table settings and touches of local artistry. While some patrons find the ambiance “okay,” others emphasize its charm as a fitting backdrop for a delightful meal. The ambience is enhanced by the gentle sounds of the ocean, creating a relaxing atmosphere to unwind after a long day of exploring.

### Menu & Culinary Experience
The menu at Ben and Sand is a delightful array of flavors, showcasing signature dishes that have left many customers raving. One standout highlighted by diners is the tandoori offerings, praised for being perfectly cooked and awe-inspiring in flavor. A particularly notable dish is the fish fry, described as crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, promising freshness that speaks volumes about the restaurant’s commitment to quality ingredients. Additionally, the seafood fried rice and Mussel fry have also found their way into happy customers’ hearts, although opinions vary on certain dishes. With a focus on affordability, the restaurant offers competitive pricing, an attractive feature that resonates with diners who are often weary of inflated tourist prices.

### Customer Experience & Service
When it comes to service, patrons have remarked on the friendly and attentive staff, often noting their willingness to ensure a satisfying dining experience. A few guests did mention a delay in receiving offbeat dish orders, typically around 10 to 15 minutes, indicating that some patience may be required for more adventurous food choices. Parking appears to be convenient, allowing for easy access even during busy hours, enhancing the overall customer experience.

### Popularity & Reviews
Social sentiment surrounding Ben and Sand is overwhelmingly positive, with many regular visitors asserting that it’s a must-visit spot whenever they return to Goa. The restaurant's reputation is bolstered by its local patronage, affirming that it is a beloved establishment among area residents. While some critiques have surfaced regarding credit card fees being charged, they seem minor compared to the overall appreciation for the dining experience.

### Utilizing Visual Content
The vibrant images provided by customers showcase not only the delectable dishes but also the inviting atmosphere of Ben and Sand. From mouthwatering presentations of tandoori specialties to beautifully plated seafood delicacies, these visuals accentuate the restaurant's commitment to a delightful culinary experience. Each photo invites viewers to imagine themselves indulging in the various offerings, from crispy chicken to rich tandoori flavors.

In conclusion, Ben and Sand stands out as a charming and affordable dining option in Colva, Goa. Whether you are a seafood lover or someone looking to dive into flavorful tandoori dishes, this restaurant promises a memorable culinary experience framed by a laid-back coastal vibe. Don't miss it during your next visit to Goa!
